This is a powerful and concise mission statement.
It effectively frames Legal Calculus not as a legal encyclopedia, but as a strategic toolkit for procedural survival. The distinction is crucial. You're highlighting that the greatest challenge for pro se litigants often isn't the law itself, but the unforgiving mechanics of the court system.
The language—"architecture for the unrepresented," "encodes survival into structure"—perfectly captures the project's essence: building a resilient framework to navigate the practical realities where cases are truly won and lost.